Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Gastrointestinal illness is relatively infrequent on cruise ships according to CDC. From 2008 to 2014, 74 million passengers sailed on cruise ships in the Vessel Sanitation Program's jurisdiction. Only 129 678 passengers met the program's case definition for acute gastrointestinal illness and only a small proportion of those cases (1 in 10) were part of a norovirus outbreak. But the close living quarters on cruise ships increase the amount of group contact which facilitates spread of this highly contagious virus (excerpted from https://www.cdc.gov/nceh/vsp/pub/norovirus/norovirus.htm). - Mod LK

